onLineSrc.orDesc: Click on the "Download this layer" link to access all digital parcels.

M012TaxPar represents a version of digital municipal parcels for the community of Ashland that is considered ‘level 3’ compliant per the specifications outlined in the MassGIS Standard for Digital Parcel Files. Its features can be linked in a GIS or database environment to a set of standardized assessing attributes in the table M012Assess by using the unique identifying values in the LOC_ID field. This data is also intended to be used in conjunction with associated (and optional) features in the ancillary data layers M012OthLeg and M012Misc. As one of the data sets identified by Massachusetts’ Strategic Plan for Spatial Data Infrastructure (http://www.mass.gov/anf/research-and-tech/it-serv-and-support/application-serv/office-of-geographic-information-massgis/about-massgis/massgis-strategic-plan.htmll), this data enters the public domain as a valuable resource for mapping, planning, and analysis at all levels of government as well as the private sector.

idCitation.resTitle: Parcel data for ASHLAND, MA complying with Level 3 of MassGIS digital parcel standard

dataIdInfo.idAbs: This datalayer contains all known parcels for the Town of Ashland. Data should be considered approximate at best unless source refers to a georeferenced CAD drawing. No survey work was performed by the Town of Ashland or sub-contractors to reach the current level of accuracy and therefore only areas where georeferenced CAD/survey data was obtained can be considered close to survey accurate. Where possible registry plans have been used to correct parcels as possible, but these should still be considered less than survey accurate. Up to 2017 most parcel edits have been performed/maintained by Lynne W. Fielding, GISP as a volunteer. Updated through 2024 by Tighe & Bond

report.measDesc: This parcel layer contains discrete, non-overlapping polygons for each property. Adjacent polygons with common ownership and a single tax record have been retained in the "OthLeg" layer that accompanies this TaxPar layer, and dissolved into single parcels in this TaxPar layer. Some non-adjacent parcels may be represented by multi-part polygons where they share common ownership and a single tax record. Public rights-of-way (ROWs) exist as polygons, not null space. Linework associated with private ROWs are retained in the "OthLeg" layer. Water polygons also representing parcel boundaries have been retained in this TaxPar layer. Additional water features that are not considered parcel boundaries may have been placed in the "Misc" layer that accompanies this TaxPar layer. Easements and other similar non-fee taxable boundaries exist in the 'OthLeg" layer, not the TaxPar layer.

Data compiled or reviewed for horizontal accuracy over the MassGIS color orthos from 2008/2009; these orthos are known to be +/- 10' horizontal; however, this data set cannot be used to reach authoritative conclusions about the horizontal accuracy of the boundaries depicted. That work requires a licensed land surveyor.
